Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Place @chicken thighs{24%ounce} on a lightly oiled
#baking sheet{}, and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the
@chorizo spice blend{1/2%tablespoon}. Bake until firm and juices run clear when
pierced with a knife, about ~{25%minutes}.

Prep the ingredients: Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice
@yellow onion{1}(diced). Core, seed, and dice @green bell pepper{2}(diced).

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a large pan on medium-high
heat. Add onions, bell peppers, and remaining @chorizo spice blend{1/2%tablespoon}.
Toss occasionally until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @basmati rice{1.5%cup} to pan along with @crushed tomatoes{1%box},
@chicken stock concentrate{2}, @honey{1%tablespoon}, and 3 cups water. Bring
to a boil, then reduce to low. Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about
~{15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped). Zest and halve
@orange{1}(zested and halved).

When rice is tender, reduce heat to low. Stir in parsley, juice of half the
orange, and a pinch of orange zest (to taste). Season with salt and pepper.
Cook uncovered, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Serve chicken on a bed of rice and enjoy!

> Jambalaya is a traditional Creole dish with rice, tomatoes, onions, green
> peppers, and some type of protein. Our chefs put a family-friendly spin on
> the dish by adding orange zest for a burst of citrus flavor and honey to
> balance out the acidity of the tomatoes.